{
  "info": {
    "name": "KSeFFlow",
    "description": "KSeFFlow (e-invoicing) API \u2014 one folder per controller. Base path /api/v1 on port 8081. Auth is the httpOnly idToken cookie set by the RegulaOne backend: log in via RegulaOne SSO first (Postman cookie jar carries it), or paste a token into {{token}} for the Bearer fallback header.\n\nAlso includes the KSeF 2.0 government API (Ministry of Finance) calls the backend makes \u2014 base {{ksefGovUrl}} (sandbox https://api-test.ksef.mf.gov.pl/v2). Those use KSeF tokens ({{ksefAuthToken}} / {{ksefAccessToken}} / {{ksefRefreshToken}}), NOT the RegulaOne session \u2014 obtain them via the Auth flow (challenge \u2192 XAdES \u2192 redeem).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8081"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "ksefGovUrl",
      "value": "https://api-test.ksef.mf.gov.pl/v2"
    },
    {
      "key": "ksefAuthToken",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "ksefAccessToken",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "ksefRefreshToken",
      "value": ""
    }
  ],
